 Udora Orizu Former Senate President and 2023 presidential aspirant,Â Bukola Saraki, will Wednesday, March 23, 2022 meet with the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) members in the House of Representatives. Saraki made this known in a notice sent to the Minority Leader of the House, Hon. Ndudi Elumelu, which was read by the Deputy Speaker, Hon. Idris Wase, at the plenary, Tuesday. In the notice, he said the meeting will be held 5pm at 50 Lobito Crescent Wuse 2, Abuja. The purpose of the meeting may be to formally inform the lawmakers of his interest to contest for Presidency in 2023. Saraki, Tuesday disclosed that some young supporters raised N40 million for his Presidential Expression of Interest and Nomination Forms. In a series of tweets on his Twitter page, the former Senate President said the youths, who are young professionals that raised the money, were convened by Abubakar Danmusa.